Get your big brother
to beat me up?

22:48.468 --> 22:50.401
- I don't need my big brother.

22:50.403 --> 22:52.136
- Oh, so you want
some too, Sally?

22:53.706 --> 22:54.672
- I'm not afraid of you.

22:54.674 --> 22:56.107
- Well maybe you should be.

22:56.109 --> 22:57.441
You're freaking weird.

22:59.912 --> 23:02.012
- Oh, look, she
tripped on a ghost.

23:02.014 --> 23:04.482
- Ghost in the graveyard,
one, two, three.

23:04.484 --> 23:06.384
- Ghost in the graveyard,
can't catch me.

23:07.420 --> 23:10.721
(melancholy piano music)

23:26.005 --> 23:28.572
(eerie music)

24:06.446 --> 24:09.680
(ominous tempo music)

24:28.568 --> 24:29.800
- Nova Scotia?

24:32.772 --> 24:34.672
- [Billy] Sally, you ready?

24:34.674 --> 24:36.006
- Yeah, just one sec.

24:40.246 --> 24:41.612
- Ready? Come on.

24:44.650 --> 24:47.718
(crickets chirping)

24:52.658 --> 24:54.225
- Poor little Tommy.

24:54.227 --> 24:55.626
He was my paper boy.

24:57.163 --> 24:59.096
- I heard the police
are investigating her.

24:59.899 --> 25:00.764
- Really?

25:01.701 --> 25:02.600
Why?

25:03.603 --> 25:05.069
- Think about it.

25:05.071 --> 25:06.804
She shows up again and
this little kid is killed

25:06.806 --> 25:08.606
at Martha's fucking grave.

25:09.509 --> 25:11.075
- I didn't think of that.

25:12.612 --> 25:14.044
- Did you see her with Reed?

25:14.046 --> 25:16.180
I can't stand that bitch.

25:16.182 --> 25:19.250
- Aren't we supposed to feel
bad for her or something?

25:19.252 --> 25:22.052
- She thinks who she
is, that's for sure.

25:22.054 --> 25:23.721
- Yeah, that's what
I want to know.

25:24.857 --> 25:28.659
Who is she and what
is her fucking deal?

25:29.795 --> 25:32.763
- Think about it, she gets
back and this kid is murdered.

25:32.765 --> 25:35.599
I mean, part of him left
on the freaking grave, man.

25:35.601 --> 25:38.135
I know you guys are friends

25:38.137 --> 25:40.104
but you gotta admit this
is some pretty freaky shit.

25:42.308 --> 25:44.875
- No, no, I know Sally.

25:44.877 --> 25:46.544
At her core I know she's good.

25:46.546 --> 25:47.745
I mean, I know that.

25:49.181 --> 25:50.614
- Whatever.

25:50.616 --> 25:52.249
- No freaking way, man.

25:52.251 --> 25:53.551
- Speaking of which,

25:54.887 --> 25:57.221
thought she was coming tonight.

25:57.223 --> 25:58.622
- [Reed] Yeah, so did I.

25:59.759 --> 26:02.626
(ominous music)

26:04.063 --> 26:07.131
(somber rock music)

26:11.938 --> 26:15.639
¶ Take it back ¶

26:15.641 --> 26:19.109
¶ Take it back ¶

26:19.111 --> 26:22.580
¶ Didn't I do it ¶

26:22.582 --> 26:25.983
¶ What did you expect ¶

26:25.985 --> 26:30.588
¶ What did you expect ¶

26:30.590 --> 26:32.957
¶ 'Cause I'm gonna
answer back like that ¶

26:32.959 --> 26:34.124
- You okay?

26:34.126 --> 26:35.025
- Yeah.

26:36.329 --> 26:37.695
- You want a beer?

26:41.000 --> 26:43.901
So hanging out with
Zoe tonight, huh?

26:43.903 --> 26:45.736
Didn't she used to
make fun of you?

26:47.139 --> 26:48.572
Just saying,

26:48.573 --> 26:50.006
I don't know why you're
hanging out with these girls.

26:50.009 --> 26:53.944
- Okay, Billy, I just wanna
be apart of the group.

26:53.946 --> 26:56.780
I just want to fit
in with everybody.

26:57.350 --> 26:59.049
You know?

26:59.051 --> 27:03.821
Not trying to be this freak
who keeps seeing a dead girl.

27:03.823 --> 27:05.255
- Okay.

27:05.257 --> 27:07.358
- Gets sent away to
wanna be protected. Like.

27:08.761 --> 27:13.697
Everybody thinks I was in like
a psych ward or whatever, so.

27:16.402 --> 27:18.235
I mean, it doesn't
even matter like.

27:19.372 --> 27:22.706
We were all kids,
so, it's whatever.

27:23.809 --> 27:24.708
I just...

27:25.711 --> 27:26.944
I just wanna be normal.

27:29.248 --> 27:30.748
- But you're not.

27:30.750 --> 27:32.349
You're special.

27:32.351 --> 27:33.984
(chuckling)

27:33.986 --> 27:37.054
(faint radio music)

27:43.796 --> 27:46.964
(ominous music)

27:46.966 --> 27:48.399
- Oh my God, Billy, stop!

27:48.401 --> 27:49.099
- [Billy] Fuck!

27:49.101 --> 27:50.434
- Oh my God!

27:50.435 --> 27:51.768
Oh my God, did you not
see her standing there?

27:51.771 --> 27:52.736
- What?!

27:52.738 --> 27:53.871
No, I didn't see anything.

27:53.873 --> 27:55.406
My fucking life
flashed before my eyes.

27:55.408 --> 27:57.107
- I'm sorry, she was
standing literally

27:57.109 --> 27:59.243
in the middle of the road.
- You almost killed us!

28:00.346 --> 28:01.712
- God, okay, I'm...

28:03.683 --> 28:04.948
Sorry.

28:04.950 --> 28:05.916
- It's all right.

28:09.789 --> 28:12.756
(thunder rumbling)

28:15.194 --> 28:18.762
(rain trickling)

28:18.764 --> 28:21.298
(ominous music)

28:55.868 --> 28:58.869
(thunder rumbling)

29:17.256 --> 29:19.823
(eerie music)

29:34.206 --> 29:37.174
(thunder rumbling)

29:42.548 --> 29:45.349
(water bubbling)

29:50.556 --> 29:53.557
(sinister music)

29:54.927 --> 29:57.895
(thunder rumbling)

30:04.904 --> 30:07.437
(ominous music)

30:34.133 --> 30:37.201
